The paper discusses combinatorial problems from various areas in AI, including Constraint Satisfaction, Global Constraints, Satisfiability, Nonmonotonic and Bayesian Reasoning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, such as Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). However, given that the paper focuses on the theoretical analysis of the power of polynomial-time preprocessing algorithms for these problems, cs.AI and cs.DS are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also possible, but less likely, as they are not directly related to the main focus of the paper.
